# ── Email / SMTP ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# IMPORTANT: This must be a Gmail APP PASSWORD, NOT your regular Gmail password.
#
# How to generate a Gmail App Password:
#   1. Go to https://myaccount.google.com/security
#   2. Enable "2-Step Verification" if not already on
#   3. Go to https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
#   4. Select app: "Mail", device: "Other" → type "Smart Inventory" → Generate
#   5. Copy the 16-character password (no spaces) and paste below
#
# If you see "Invalid login" or "Username and Password not accepted":
#   → Your App Password is wrong or expired — regenerate it at the URL above
#
# If you see "EDNS" or "getaddrinfo EAI_AGAIN":
#   → Your server/hosting provider is blocking outbound SMTP (port 587)
#   → Contact your host to allow smtp.gmail.com:587, or switch to port 465
#
